HEADWORD: Hedgerow
<hw>Hedge"row`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A row of shrubs, or
trees, planted for inclosure or separation of fields.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By <qex>hedgerow</qex> elms and hillocks green.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hedging bill</ent>⟦br⟧
